# Group Video Call Grid Layout Redesign (WhatsApp-Style)

The current group video call grid layout needs to be redesigned to provide a better viewing experience similar to WhatsApp, Google Meet, Microsoft Teams, or Discord. And also when the late user tries to join the call via the join now message in the chat, the app crashes saying 'flowlink keeps stopping' this happens only for the mobile app.

## Current Problems

### 1. Web Layout (Image 1)

#### Issue A: Host Video is Too Large

* The host's own video occupies nearly half of the screen.
* This wastes screen space and reduces the visibility of other participants.
* In group calls, users are primarily interested in seeing other participants rather than their own camera feed.

#### Issue B: Participant Tiles Are Too Vertical

* The current layout stacks participants into tall vertical rectangles.
* Faces are cropped or difficult to view.
* If 4 or more users join, the tiles become even narrower and taller, making video viewing worse.

### Desired Behavior

* Use a responsive grid layout.
* Prioritize displaying remote participants.
* Show participant videos in landscape-oriented tiles.
* The local user's video should either:

  * Appear as a small floating picture-in-picture overlay, or
  * Be displayed in the same grid size as others.

---

### 2. Mobile Layout (Image 2)

#### Current Issue

* Large portions of the screen remain empty and unused.
* Participant video tiles are extremely small.
* Most of the screen is occupied by blank space instead of video content.

### Desired Behavior

* Video tiles should automatically expand to use available screen space.
* The grid should dynamically resize based on participant count.
* Empty areas should be minimized.

---

